        <example xml:id="auto_c1rqdgxl">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_vb3o4dug">
                    Find the tangent in the indicated angle below.
                </p>
                <image width="50%">
                <latex-image label="Triangle8">
                    \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=2,black]
                         % Define points
                        \coordinate (A) at (0,0);
                        \coordinate (B) at (6,0);
                        \coordinate (C) at (3,5);
                        \coordinate (D) at (3,0); % Foot of the perpendicular

                        % Draw triangle
                        \draw [very thick,fill=white] (A) -- (B) -- (C) -- cycle;
                        
                        % Draw height
                        \draw [very thick,dashed] (C) -- (D);
                        
                        % Right angle symbol at D
                        \draw [very thick](D) ++(-0.3,0) -- ++(0,0.3) -- ++(0.3,0);

                        % Draw angle arcs
                        \draw [very thick,blue](A) ++(0.8,0) arc (0:60:0.8); % Alpha (angle CAD)
                        \draw [very thick,blue](C) ++(-0.3,-0.5) arc (200:300:0.2); % Theta (angle ACD)

                        % Labels
                        \node[left] at (A) {\huge{$A$}};
                        \node[above] at (C) {\huge{$C$}};
                        \node[below] at (B) {\huge{$B$}};
                        \node[below] at (D) {\huge{$D$}};
                        
                        % Side lengths
                        \node[above left] at (1.5,2.5) {\huge{$5$ cm}};
                        \node[above right] at (4.5,2.5) {\huge{$5$ cm}};
                        \node[below] at (1.5,0) {\huge{$3$ cm}};
                        \node[below] at (4.5,0) {\huge{$3$ cm}};
                        
                        % Angle labels
                        \node at (0.9,0.4) {\huge{$\alpha$}};  % Alpha near A
                        \node [right]at (2.5,4) {\huge{$\theta$}}; % Theta near C
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                    
                </image>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p xml:id="auto_91wfy76p">
                    The first thing you should do is to calculate the perpendicular height of the Triangle then identify the opposite and the adjacent sides of angle 
                    <m> \theta</m> and angle <m>\alpha</m>. Finaly find there tangents.
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_o1ytcte3">
                    Finding the perpendicular height.

                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_waeoaelq">
                    We use pythagorean relationship that is <me>H^2=b^2+h^2</me>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_dcwph91i">
                    <md>
                        <mrow> h^2=\amp H^2-b^2 </mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp 5^2=3^2</mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp 25-9 </mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp 16 </mrow>
                        <mrow>\sqrt{h^2}= \amp \sqrt{16} </mrow>
                        <mrow>h= \amp 4\,cm </mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                
                <p xml:id="auto_0b0rrrhp">
                    Finding <m>\text{tan} \theta</m>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_4u7e5lyk">
                    <m>\text{tan} \, \theta =  \frac{\text{Opposite }}{\text{Adjacent }}</m>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_jwai25jb">
                    The opposite side <m>=3\,cm</m>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_0sms4pqu">
                    The adjacent side <m>=4\,cm</m>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_1s6pl7mn">
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{tan} \, \theta= \amp \frac{3\,cm}{4\,cm} </mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp  \frac{3}{4}</mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp 0.75</mrow>
                        
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_wrm2ivke">
                    Finding <m>\text{tan} \alpha</m>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_bzwoz7is">
                    <m>\text{tan} \, \alpha =  \frac{\text{Opposite }}{\text{Adjacent }}</m>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_er5902yy">
                    The opposite side <m>=4\,cm</m>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_jmn1z7yo">
                    The adjacent side <m>=3\,cm</m>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_62ylhnkb">
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{tan} \, \theta= \amp \frac{4\,cm}{3\,cm} </mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp  \frac{4}{3}</mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp  1.3333333333</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp  1\frac{1}{3}</mrow>
                        
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_yyt8sayb">
                    Therefore,
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_7d3ghbtj">
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{tan} \, \theta= \amp 0.75</mrow>
                        <mrow> \text{tan} \, \alpha=\amp 1.333</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                    
                
            </solution>
            
        </example>


